    "Tumors intersecting the ventricles showed a large positive DAS, although nonsignificant (Fig. 2g TOP; p = 0.31, one-tailed U-test).",
    "However, given its larger magnitude and greater significance with respect to all other groups, we provide a possible explanation of its meaning in the discussion.",
    "A logistic regression also displayed a reasonable determination coefficient and pattern (R 2 = 0.8), but the small number of periventricular tumors did not allow for further quantitative assessment (Fig. 2g BOTTOM).",
    "As a final note, we report that the tumor with the highest DAS was a grade II ependymoma located in the temporal lobe and intersecting with the left lateral ventricle.",
    "The tumor with the lowest (and negative) DAS corresponded with a grade I meningioma located in the frontal-skull base not intersecting the ventricles."
